<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Length, 9.0-12.0 mm. Head orange, except medial black stripe on vertex extending anteriorly through ocelli and anterior to ocelli as an inverted V (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Euxiphydria leucopoda, holotype 1 Dorsal view 2 Lateral view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, front view 5 Thorax, dorsal view 6 Thorax, lateral view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11318" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
). Antenna dark brown with scape and pedicel reddish; Thorax black with tegula, anteroventral quarter and narrow posterior margin of pronotum white (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Euxiphydria leucopoda, holotype 1 Dorsal view 2 Lateral view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, front view 5 Thorax, dorsal view 6 Thorax, lateral view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11318" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figs 2, 5</figureCitation>
). Abdomen black with white spot laterally on eighth tergite (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Euxiphydria leucopoda, holotype 1 Dorsal view 2 Lateral view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, front view 5 Thorax, dorsal view 6 Thorax, lateral view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11318" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Legs entirely white 
<pageBreakToken pageId="3" pageNumber="4" start="start">to</pageBreakToken>
yellow except apex of apical tarsomeres brownish (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Euxiphydria leucopoda, holotype 1 Dorsal view 2 Lateral view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, front view 5 Thorax, dorsal view 6 Thorax, lateral view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11318" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Wings hyaline, veins and stigma black (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Euxiphydria leucopoda, holotype 1 Dorsal view 2 Lateral view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, front view 5 Thorax, dorsal view 6 Thorax, lateral view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11318" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Antenna with 13 antennomeres; length of first four antennomeres as 1.0:0.4:0.8:0.5. Frons sculpture reticulate, especially around and anterior to ocelli (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Euxiphydria leucopoda, holotype 1 Dorsal view 2 Lateral view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, front view 5 Thorax, dorsal view 6 Thorax, lateral view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11318" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
). Head from above strongly narrowing behind eyes, distance behind eye less than eye length (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Euxiphydria leucopoda, holotype 1 Dorsal view 2 Lateral view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, front view 5 Thorax, dorsal view 6 Thorax, lateral view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11318" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Malar space between eye and antennal groove much narrower than groove. Axilla and mesoscutellum with irregular longitudinal carinae; lateral and posterior downturned areas smooth and shiny (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Euxiphydria leucopoda, holotype 1 Dorsal view 2 Lateral view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head, front view 5 Thorax, dorsal view 6 Thorax, lateral view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11318" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Hind basitarsomere slightly longer than length of remaining tarsomeres combined. Lengths of sheath and basal plate subequal. Male unknown.
</paragraph>
